						               													<description>Questions pour un Champion is a French game based on the TV show of the same name. Played from 3 to 5 players it is a game that tests both your knowledge and your reflex.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the first round all the players are obliged to answer questions by pushing a special button before anyone else does. The goal is to score 9 points which takes a player to the second round. The player that didn't reach 9 points when everyone else did is eliminated.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the second round each remaining player chooses one of four proposed subjects and has to answer questions related to it. The maximum score here is 4 points (for 4 consecutive correct answers). The best two players go through to the final.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the last round the two remaining players are face to face, having to find the answer for some long questions read by the presenter. The players may score 4, 3, 2 or 1 point, based on the number of information given by the presenter. The first player to score 9 points is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
